Note:
GENERATOR<T> - Coroutine-style producer of values.

A Generator wraps a producer function that yields values lazily. Each call
to generator_next either produces the next value or signals exhaustion.

This is implemented as a stack-resumable iterator backed by a channel and
a producer thread. The producer thread pushes values into the channel;
generator_next pulls from the channel.

Generator layout (40 bytes):
  offset 0:  channel_ptr   (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  producer_fn   (8 bytes)
  offset 16: producer_data (8 bytes)
  offset 24: thread_id     (8 bytes)
  offset 32: state         (8 bytes) (0=created, 1=running, 2=completed)

Dependencies:
- concurrency/channel.runa
- threading/thread_core.runa
- memory/layout.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/concurrency/channel.runa" as Chan
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/threading/thread_core.runa" as ThreadCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Mem

Constant GEN_OFF_CHANNEL as Integer is 0
Constant GEN_OFF_PRODUCER as Integer is 8
Constant GEN_OFF_DATA as Integer is 16
Constant GEN_OFF_THREAD as Integer is 24
Constant GEN_OFF_STATE as Integer is 32
Constant GEN_STRUCT_SIZE as Integer is 40

Constant GEN_STATE_CREATED as Integer is 0
Constant GEN_STATE_RUNNING as Integer is 1
Constant GEN_STATE_COMPLETED as Integer is 2

Constant GEN_OK as Integer is 1
Constant GEN_DONE as Integer is 0
Constant GEN_ERR_INVALID as Integer is -1

@Reasoning
Create a generator that will produce values via the supplied producer
function. The producer signature is takes (channel_ptr, data_ptr) returns Integer
and is expected to channel_send values then channel_close at exhaustion.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate the generator, create a bounded channel (capacity 16 by default
to provide backpressure), store the producer pointer + data.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One alloc + one channel create.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
producer_fn must remain valid until generator_destroy.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generator_create" takes producer_fn as Integer, producer_data as Integer returns Integer:
    Let g be proc allocate from Memory with GEN_STRUCT_SIZE
    If g is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ch be proc channel_create from Chan with 16
    If ch is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Memory with g
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_CHANNEL, ch
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_PRODUCER, producer_fn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_DATA, producer_data
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_THREAD, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_STATE, GEN_STATE_CREATED
    Return g
End Process

@Reasoning
Push a value into the generator's output channel. Called by the producer
function from its own thread.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Channel-send a value pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One channel send.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Called from the producer side.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generator_yield" takes g as Integer, value_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If g is equal to 0:
        Return GEN_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let ch be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_CHANNEL
    Return proc channel_send from Chan with ch, value_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
Producer signals completion. Closes the channel so generator_next returns
GEN_DONE.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Channel-close the output channel and mark generator as completed.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One channel close.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generator_complete" takes g as Integer returns Integer:
    If g is equal to 0:
        Return GEN_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let ch be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_CHANNEL
    proc channel_close from Chan with ch
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_STATE, GEN_STATE_COMPLETED
    Return GEN_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Consumer pulls the next value. Blocks until the producer yields or
completes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Channel-receive from the output channel. Translate channel return code
into GEN_OK / GEN_DONE.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One channel receive.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
out_value_holder must point to writable 8-byte storage.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generator_next" takes g as Integer, out_value_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If g is equal to 0:
        Return GEN_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    If out_value_holder is equal to 0:
        Return GEN_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let ch be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_CHANNEL
    Let rc be proc channel_receive from Chan with ch, out_value_holder
    If rc is equal to 1:
        Return GEN_OK
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with out_value_holder, 0, 0
    Return GEN_DONE
End Process

Process called "generator_destroy" takes g as Integer returns Integer:
    If g is equal to 0:
        Return GEN_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let ch be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with g, GEN_OFF_CHANNEL
    If ch is not equal to 0:
        proc channel_close from Chan with ch
        proc channel_destroy from Chan with ch
    End If
    proc deallocate from Memory with g
    Return GEN_OK
End Process
